#theorem[
  Given $F in "AC"([a, b])$, $F$ is constant on $[a, b]$, that is, there is some $c in RR$ such that $F(x) = c$ for every $x in [a, b]$ if and only if $F' = 0$ a.e. on $[a, b]$.
